<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910214-0105</DOCNO><DOCID>910214-0105.</DOCID><HL>   TransAlta Utilities Plant</HL><DATE>02/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11</SO><CO>   T.TAU MD</CO><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><LP>   CALGARY, Alberta -- TransAlta Utilities Corp. said itplans to build a plant to produce thermal energy andelectricity near Toronto, at a cost of about $86.7 million.   It said the natural-gas fueled plant in Mississauga,Ontario, is scheduled for completion late next year. It willsupply heat to a McDonnell Douglas Corp. manufacturing plantand 110 megawatts of electricity to Ontario Hydro, aprovincially owned utility.</LP><TEXT>   TransAlta is a regulated electric utility. It said theMississauga plant will be built, owned and operated by anon-regulated subsidiary, TransAlta Resources Corp. en</TEXT></DOC>